This topic describes how to install and configure Ops Manager before deploying <%= vars.product_full %> on Google Cloud Platform (GCP).

## <a id='prerequisites'></a>Prerequisites

You use Ops Manager to install and configure <%= vars.product_short %>.
Before you install Ops Manager, review [GCP Prerequisites and Resource Requirements](gcp-requirements.html).

## <a id="install-om"></a>Install and Configure Ops Manager

Multiple versions of Ops Manager are compatible with each version of <%= vars.product_short %>.
To confirm that your Ops Manager version is compatible with the version of <%= vars.product_short %> that you want to install,
see the <a href="release-notes.html"><%= vars.product_short %> Release Notes</a>.

To install and configure Ops Manager, follow either the manual or Terraform instructions in the table below.

<p class="note warning"><strong>Warning:</strong> The Terraform templates described in this topic are not supported and are not recommended for use.
Advanced users can install Ops Manager with Terraform using <a href="https://github.com/pivotal/paving">paving</a> in GitHub. 
You might need to modify your Terraform template configuration based on your unique platform needs.
</p>

